The paper deals with information flow analysis, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The methodology proposed in the paper involves experimental science and statistical analysis, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses causal inference, which is a topic in statistics and machine learning, and can be categorized under cs.SI (social and information networks). Finally, the paper deals with data usage by websites, which can be considered a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CY).
